President Cyril Ramaphosa chairing a virtual Presidential Coordinating Council (PCC) meeting from his private residence in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has chaired a virtual meeting of the President’s Coordinating Council from his private residence in Johannesburg.
This is to drive home the message that South Africans should stay in their houses during the 21-day lockdown. The meeting was co-chaired by Deputy President David Mabuza, and included ministers, premiers and the South African Local Government Association. READ: Stay at home: SA medical practitioners plead The focus of the meeting was to discuss the implementation of lockdown measures. It also looked at strategies toward economic recovery. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.